Tickets for the annual ScaleConf event in Cape Town have gone on sale. ScaleConf aims to bring international and local experts together to share their experience scaling websites and services using modern technologies and philosophies. Now in its sixth year, the event is scheduled for 9-10 March and takes place in the Kirstenbosch Botanical Gardens. Tickets cost R1,500. Included in the ticket price is access to the main event, featuring international and African speakers, lunch, and coffee and other refreshments. There will also be evening events to network.